         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">March 28/70 ¶ Dear Mueller ¶  ¶ Thanks for yours of 6/11/69 &amp; 4/12. Thozet asks me to send you  ¶ Artemisia Dracunculus ¶  of which I am trying to get seed for you ¶  ¶ I sent you a bag of Argania see...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.03.28b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">March 28/70</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mueller<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Pentzia virgata I have from McOwan'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thanks for yours of 6/11/69 &amp; 4/12. Thozet asks me to send you <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Artemisia%20Dracunculus">Artemisia Dracunculus</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> of which I am trying to get seed for you</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I sent you a bag of <name key="Argania">Argania</name> seeds, it should be a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">most</hi>
               </seg> valuable thing for your Colony in droughts especially.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>More big <name key="Todea">Todea</name>s will be most acceptable — it is growing famously.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am most anxious to know how the Nepenthes and the Sarraceniae got out</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will see about sending <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Aconite">Aconite</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> roots next winter<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J, Hooker, 14 August 1869 (in this edition as 69-08-14c).</p>
               </note> — it is too late this spring — ask again by next winter for what you most want &amp; I will send them in damp moss overland.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have sent <name key="Eriophorum">Eriophorum</name>, <name key="Sagittaria">Sagittaria</name>, <name key="Butomus">Butomus</name> &amp;c in the cases already.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Hooker to M, 8 December 1869.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regard to your animadversion on the Cape for not sending big <name key="Todea">Todea</name>s,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 6 November 1869 (in this edition as 69-11-06a).</p>
               </note> — they do not grow big there — we have had their state of the plants for 30 years in growth.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I can send you Cork plants in a Wards case, a little later it is too cold yet for Wards cases.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Sincerely Yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
